Sentencas: A simulation of a nickel-yttrium stabilized zirconium oxide (Ni-YSZ) solid oxide fuel cell cermet anode was used to determine the electronic current distribution within the percolating networks of nickel particles distributed in the electrode.
Titulo: Electronic Current Distribution Calculation for a Ni-YSZ Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anode

Sentencas: The anode is simulated via a MonteCarlo percolation model and current distribution is calculated via a relaxation algorithm.
Titulo: Electronic Current Distribution Calculation for a Ni-YSZ Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anode

Sentencas: Nickel particle current densities are reported as a ratio to the total anode current density allowing results to be applied to any anode current density.
Titulo: Electronic Current Distribution Calculation for a Ni-YSZ Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anode

Sentencas: Calculated current distributions were drastically affected by the volume percent of nickel as well as anode porosity.
Titulo: Electronic Current Distribution Calculation for a Ni-YSZ Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anode

Sentencas: Experiments were performed to determine failure current densities of thin nickel wires to establish the relationship between critical current densities and surface area or volume of the wires.
Titulo: Electronic Current Distribution Calculation for a Ni-YSZ Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anode

Sentencas: Both reducing and oxidizing environments were used for these measurements over a temperature range up to 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Electronic Current Distribution Calculation for a Ni-YSZ Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Anode
